inal and ambitious 1998 Acheson Inquiry into health inequalities, and the theoretical and methodological issues underpinning health inequalities. The contributors consider the determinants of inequality - for example, early childhood experience and ethnicity - the factors that mediate the relationship between determinants and health - nutrition, housing and health behaviour - and the sectoral policy interventions in user involvement, local area partnership working and social work. Challenging health inequalities offers a combination of broad analysis of progress from differing perspectives and will be key reading to academics, students and policy makers.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Jan 2023) 0aHealth services accessibilityzGreat Britain. 0aMedical policyzGreat Britain. 0aPoorxHealth and hygienezGreat Britain. 0aPublic healthzGreat Britain. 7aMEDICAL / Epidemiology.2bisacsh1 aBeresford, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBradby, Hannah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBywaters, Paul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCalnan, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCaraher, Martin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCarpenter, Mick, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChandola, Tarani, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCroft, Suzy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDolan, Alan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDorling, Danny, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDowler, Elizabeth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDowler, Elizabeth, eeditor